review_blob: Im a big fan of hefe weisse and bocks, but this one is simply almost undrinkable. Very sour, yet thin taste that is almost unbearable to start with but your mouth will tolerate it a bit better after a couple of sips. The taste makes you want to double check the best before date on the bottle - more than once!! Simply one of the worst tasting experiences in a long time.

Simply smoke! Not much wheat beer characteristics at all. An interesting 
concept, but does not work as it stands.

A swetish, but very nice strong/old ale. A gem in its class. Strong in alcohol, but 
that does not spoil the taste.

This not really a porter, more like stout.
The flavour says "burnt rye bread" to me.
Not really my favourite
A fruity and flowery, nicely hopped "summer ale". Almost perfect in its class.
